Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
It should be better for freshman to live on campus dorm during the first year of college. First it provides more opportunities to familiar with the people and environment around school, which could makes them enter into study soon. The other reason is that it is safe while living in school. When we arrive at a new place safety is the most important thing we need to concern.